orchestra /ˈɔːkɪstrə/

(orchestras) 

1. N-COUNT An orchestra is a large group of musicians who play a variety of different instruments together. Orchestras usually play classical music. 管弦乐队 

例： ...the Los Angeles Philharmonic Orchestra. …洛杉矶爱乐乐团。 

2.  →  see also symphony orchestra 

3. N-SING The orchestra or the orchestra seats in a theatre or concert hall are the seats on the first floor directly in front of the stage. 舞台前方一楼座位 [美国英语] 

例： With the balcony blocked off, patrons filled most of the orchestra seats. 楼厅包厢被封闭了，赞助人几乎坐满了舞台前方的一楼座位。

